  "prompt": "Is morning sickness a sign of good pregnancy?",
  "response": "Morning sickness, which typically includes nausea and vomiting, is a common symptom experienced by many pregnant individuals, particularly during the first trimester. While the exact cause of morning sickness isn't fully understood, it is believed to be related to hormonal changes occurring in the body during pregnancy, particularly increased levels of human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG) and progesterone.\n\nMany healthcare providers view morning sickness as a sign that the body is responding to pregnancy hormones, which can indicate a viable pregnancy. However, the presence or absence of morning sickness does not definitively determine the health or outcome of a pregnancy. Some individuals may experience severe morning sickness (known as hyperemesis gravidarum), while others may not experience it at all, and both can have healthy pregnancies.\n\nIf you have concerns about morning sickness or any other aspect of your pregnancy, it\u2019s always best to consult with a healthcare provider for personalized guidance and support.",
